Diagnosis. This species is characterized by the uncus with two curved and thorn-shaped lateral processes, distal process of the gnathos short column-shaped and serrated at apex, and sclerotized sub-rectangular median plate obtusely rounded on the outer margin in the male genitalia ( Fig. 4 ). It is similar to
L. furciillatusa
Wang, Chen & Wu, 2019
in wing pattern and the male genitalia, and the differences between the two species are stated in the diagnosis of
L. furciillatusa
.
